{
  "signal_description": "Calculate the on-time delivery rate for each month. The query is performed on the 'defaultview-290' table. The 'Month' column is derived by truncating the 'end_time' column to the month level. The 'CASE_ID' column is used to count the number of cases. The numerator of the on-time delivery rate is the count of cases where the 'DeliveryGoodsMovementOnTime' column is 'Yes' and there is at least one event with the name 'Create Outbound Delivery'. The denominator is the total count of cases. The result is multiplied by 100 to get the percentage. The result is ordered by the 'Month' column in ascending order and filled with null values for missing months."
}
